//@version=6
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// 🧠 GodTier_ContextEngine v1.4.1
// Published library version: GodTier_ContextEngine/7
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Multi-Layer Market Context Intelligence Engine
// Sits above every signal in the GOD_TIER_VP suite as the arbiter:
// reads all 6 intelligence layers, weights them, scores 0–100, classifies
// the market phase, and gates signals accordingly.
//
// CHANGELOG v1.3.2 → v1.4.0
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// PATCH #33 — Phase 3: Prior VA Context Integration.
//   L2 Volume Profile scorer now incorporates previous session levels.
//   - 80% Rule Context: Boosts score when price is accepted inside prior VA.
//   - NPOC Magnet: Scores untraded POCs from prior sessions as targets.
//   - Rejection/Acceptance: Adds directional bias based on prior VA interaction.
//   - Confluence: Reinforces breakouts that clear both current and prior VAH.
//   API change: f_score_vp and analyze_context signatures expanded.
//   Breaking change for all importers.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v1.3.1 → v1.3.2
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// PATCH #28 — gate_structure_break: split CHoCH / BOS gate requirement.
//   CHoCH is a regime-change signal — it fires because the market is
//   LEAVING consolidation. Requiring signal_gate == "OPEN" to render it
//   is self-defeating: OPEN requires composite >= 70 which requires the
//   market to already be trending — the exact thing CHoCH is announcing.
//   BOS (trend continuation) correctly requires OPEN (confirming an
//   already-trending environment). CHoCH now requires gate != "CLOSED"
//   (CAUTION is sufficient) + same L-score minimums (L1≥55, L5≥40, L3≥35).
//   API change: gate_structure_break(is_choch=false). Callers that pass
//   true get the relaxed CAUTION-ok rule; callers that omit the param
//   (default false = BOS) keep the original OPEN-required behavior.
//   No other gate methods changed.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v1.3 → v1.3.1
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// PATCH #3 — f_classify_phase: SMD early-session warmup gate.
//   During EMA warmup, composite < 40 AND l3 <= 50 can be simultaneously
//   true, causing valid DISTRIBUTION/ACCUMULATION events to fall through
//   to RANGING_NOISE and close the gate. Added dual-threshold: l3 > 50
//   when composite >= 40 (normal), l3 > 20 when composite < 40 (warmup).
// PATCH #4 — f_score_momentum (L5): delta_strength contribution halved
//   (12.5 pts max, was 25). Same input already contributes 20 pts in L3.
//   Double-counting across L3 (weight 25%) + L5 (weight 15%) was inflating
//   composite by up to 8.75 pts from a single signal.
// PATCH #5 — f_score_liquidity (L4): added `not hi_conv_bull/bear` guard
//   to ifvg_flip additions, consistent with existing fa_bull/fa_bear pattern.
//   Prevents L4 hitting 80 on compound SWEEP+FA+IFVG bars and forcing
//   max composite regardless of L2/L3 state.
// PATCH #9 — build_dashboard_str: annotated as dead code / unverified.
//   Method is exported but never called by GOD_TIER_VP main script.
// PATCH #10 — f_top_driver: documented intentional STRUCTURE tie-break bias.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// CHANGELOG v1.2 → v1.3
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// FIX 1 — L5 Momentum: replaced bool ma_fast_above_med with int ma_partial_align.
//          A two-MA relationship has three distinct states (fast > med, fast < med,
//          flat/entangled/na). A bool can only encode two, making the "entangled"
//          state unreachable — the prior `else if not ma_fast_above_med` branch
//          was always true when reached, identical to the original broken else.
//          int ma_partial_align encodes all three states directly:
//            1  = fast > med  → partial bull, 18 pts, bias  1
//           -1  = fast < med  → partial bear, 18 pts, bias -1
//            0  = flat / na   → indeterminate, 0 pts,  bias  0
//          All three branches are now genuinely reachable. BREAKING CHANGE:
//          any caller passing bool must update to the tri-state int derivation
//          shown in the integration patch. Publish as library version 2.
//
// REFACTOR 2 — gate_* functions converted to methods on ContextState (v6 syntax).
//          All five gate functions and build_dashboard_str are now `export method`
//          on ContextState. Call site changes from ctx_eng.gate_fvg(cie_state)
//          to cie_state.gate_fvg() — more idiomatic and removes the namespace
//          prefix. No logic changes.
//
// REFACTOR 3 — f_classify_phase no longer recomputes bull/bear votes.
//          analyze_context pre-computes bull_votes and bear_votes (integer counts,
//          distinct from the weighted floats used for conflict detection) and
//          passes them directly into f_classify_phase. Removes redundant
//          5-bias recount that happened every bar inside the classifier.
//          f_classify_phase signature shrinks by 5 parameters.
//
// REFACTOR 4 — ContextState.new() uses named field initialization.
//          Long positional constructor call replaced with named fields. Safe
//          against future field insertion/reordering in the type definition.
//
// NOTE    — _smooth_comp var singleton caveat documented in analyze_context.
//
// CHANGELOG v1.1 → v1.2
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// FIX 1 — L5 Momentum: Repaired `else` branch logic trap.
//          Previous code fired `score += 18 / bias := -1` on ANY case where
//          ma_bull_aligned, ma_bear_aligned, and ma_fast_above_med were all
//          false — including entangled/flat MAs with no real bear signal.
//          Now uses explicit `else if not ma_fast_above_med` (partial bear)
//          with true fallthrough `// else` scoring 0 / bias 0 for neutral MAs.
//
// FIX 2 — L3 OrderFlow: Semantic floor for conflicted+exhausted state.
//          ds_fp_conflict (-10) + exhaustion (-8) could combine to -18 before
//          f_clamp(), making deeply conflicted flow invisible (score=0) —
//          identical to the "no order flow data" case. A math.max(5.0) floor
//          is now applied when any meaningful OF input was non-default, so
//          "contradictory signal present" is distinguishable from "no signal."
//
// FIX 3 — f_classify_phase: CHoCH override hardened against stale persistence.
//          CHoCH now only promotes to STRUCTURE_FLIP when l1 > 20. A CHoCH
//          firing with degraded structure score indicates multi-bar persistence
//          and falls through to lower-priority phase logic instead of
//          overriding a high-composite trending environment.
//
// FIX 4 — f_classify_phase: DISTRIBUTION/ACCUMULATION priority raised.
//          SMD checks now evaluate BEFORE TRENDING_ALIGNED. Previously,
//          composite >= 75 + bull_votes >= 4 suppressed active DISTRIBUTION
//          labels entirely — hiding the exact institutional signal the system
//          was built to surface. SMD gating on l3 > 50 remains to prevent
//          low-conviction fires.
//
// FIX 5 — gate_structure_break: STRUCTURE_FLIP bypass added.
//          STRUCTURE_FLIP phases now open the gate unconditionally, bypassing
//          the conflict check. CHoCH fires as conflict resolves — the
//          transitional bar often still has conflict=true, which previously
//          blocked the gate on the bar you most needed it open.
//
// FIX 6 — L6 Session: Instrument-aware expected_bars for 24h assets.
//          Previous 390min (US RTH) assumption produced wrong age_pct on
//          BTCUSD and forex — 15m BTC got expected_bars=26 vs correct 96.
//          Now uses syminfo.type: crypto/forex → 1440min, equities/futures
//          → 390min. Directly fixes L6 accuracy on BTCUSD (your primary chart).
//
// CHANGELOG v1.0 → v1.1
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// FIX 1 — L6 Session: removed va_state double-count. va_state is already
//          fully scored in L2 (25 pts). L6 is now a pure timing filter
//          (session age curve only) to avoid inflating Contracting/Expanding
//          across two independent layers.
//
// FIX 2 — Conflict detection: switched from raw unweighted vote counts to
//          layer-weight-aware conflict scoring. L6 excluded from conflict
//          detection (it is directionally neutral by design). Threshold
//          tightened: conflict fires when weighted disagreement is ≤ 0.15
//          (was any 1-vote spread in a 5-layer raw count).
//
// FIX 3 — RANGING_NOISE threshold: changed from abs(votes) <= 1 to
//          votes == 0 (strictly tied). A 3-2 weighted lean is a real
//          directional signal, not noise.
//
// FIX 4 — L4 Liquidity: removed 15-pt no-event floor. When no liquidity
//          event fires, L4 now correctly scores 0, allowing f_top_driver
//          to accurately reflect when liquidity is genuinely absent.
//
// FIX 5 — L3 Order Flow: added SMD mutual exclusion guard. If smd_dist
//          and smd_accum both fire simultaneously (data conflict), score
//          receives a small neutral bonus with no directional bias commit.
//
// FIX 6 — Composite smoothing: added lightweight EMA (0.7/0.3) on the
//          composite score before gate and high_conviction evaluation.
//          Prevents bar-to-bar gate flipping from boolean-heavy inputs.
//          Raw composite still stored in ContextState.score for the HUD.
//
// LAYERS (weights):
//   L1 Structure      25%  — ZigZag, BOS/CHoCH, swing bias, quality scores
//   L2 Volume Profile 20%  — POC, VA position, profile shape, VA breathing
//   L3 Order Flow     25%  — CVD, delta strength, flow pressure, absorption,
//                            exhaustion, iceberg, divergence, SMD, imbalances
//   L4 Liquidity      10%  — ZZ sweeps, failed auctions, IFVG polarity
//   L5 Momentum       15%  — MA alignment, rotation factor, delta acceleration
//   L6 Session         5%  — Session timing curve (instrument-aware)
//
// OUTPUT per bar:
//   ContextState.phase        → string label: TRENDING_ALIGNED, RANGING_NOISE, etc.
//   ContextState.score        → float 0–100 composite conviction
//   ContextState.bias         →  1 bull / -1 bear / 0 neutral
//   ContextState.high_conviction → score >= threshold (default 70)
//   ContextState.signal_gate  → "OPEN" / "CAUTION" / "CLOSED"
//   ContextState.phase_color  → display color for HUD
//   Per-layer sub-scores for radar/bar HUD
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

library("GodTier_ContextEngine", overlay=true)
// Version: 7
// Suite semantic version: 1.4.1


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// TYPE DEFINITIONS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// @type Full context state output — one instance per bar.
export type ContextState
    // ── Core outputs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    string  phase            // Market phase classification string
    float   score            // Composite conviction score 0–100
    int     bias             //  1=bull  -1=bear  0=neutral
    bool    high_conviction  // score >= conviction_threshold
    string  signal_gate      // "OPEN" / "CAUTION" / "CLOSED"
    color   phase_color      // Color for HUD / labels

    // ── Layer sub-scores (0–100 each) for HUD radar ───────────────────────
    float   l1_structure
    float   l2_vp
    float   l3_orderflow
    float   l4_liquidity
    float   l5_momentum
    float   l6_session

    // ── Metadata ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    string  top_driver       // Which layer is driving the score
    bool    conflict_detected // Layers disagree on direction


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// INTERNAL HELPER: safe normalize to 0–100
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
f_clamp(float v) =>
    math.max(0.0, math.min(100.0, v))


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// L1 — STRUCTURE INTELLIGENCE SCORER
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// @param score_long   float   ZigZag structure quality score for longs (0–100)
// @param score_short  float   ZigZag structure quality score for shorts (0–100)
// @param struct_bias  int     ZZ structural bias: 1=bull -1=bear 0=neutral
// @param bull_bos     bool    BOS fired in bull direction this bar
// @param bear_bos     bool    BOS fired in bear direction this bar
// @param bull_choch   bool    CHoCH fired in bull direction this bar
// @param bear_choch   bool    CHoCH fired in bear direction this bar
// @param hi_conv_bull bool    SWEEP+FA high-conviction bull event
// @param hi_conv_bear bool    SWEEP+FA high-conviction bear event
// @returns [score 0–100, directional_bias 1/-1/0]
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
export f_score_structure(
    float score_long,
    float score_short,
    int   struct_bias,
    bool  bull_bos,
    bool  bear_bos,
    bool  bull_choch,
    bool  bear_choch,
    bool  hi_conv_bull,
    bool  hi_conv_bear) =>

    // Base: use whichever directional quality score is dominant
    float base = struct_bias == 1  ? score_long  :
                 struct_bias == -1 ? score_short :
                 math.max(score_long, score_short) * 0.6   // neutral = penalized

    // Event bonuses
    float bonus = 0.0
    bonus += (bull_choch or bear_choch) ? 20.0 : 0.0   // CHoCH is high-signal
    bonus += (bull_bos   or bear_bos)   ? 10.0 : 0.0   // BOS continuation bonus
    bonus += (hi_conv_bull or hi_conv_bear) ? 15.0 : 0.0  // SWEEP+FA max bonus

    // Bias value for CIE
    int bias = struct_bias != 0 ? struct_bias :
               (hi_conv_bull or bull_choch or bull_bos) ? 1  :
               (hi_conv_bear or bear_choch or bear_bos) ? -1 : 0

    [f_clamp(base + bonus), bias]


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// L2 — VOLUME PROFILE INTELLIGENCE SCORER
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// @param poc          float   Point of Control price
// @param vah          float   Value Area High price
// @param val          float   Value Area Low price
// @param profile_shape string "P" / "b" / "D" / "Balanced"
// @param va_state     string  "Expanding" / "Contracting" / "Stable" / "Neutral"
// @param skewness     float   Profile skewness ratio (1.0 = balanced)
// @param price        float   Current price (close)
// @param atr          float   Current ATR for proximity logic
// @returns [score 0–100, directional_bias 1/-1/0]
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
export f_score_vp(
    float  poc,
    float  vah,
    float  val,
    string profile_shape,
    string va_state,
    float  skewness,
    float  price,
    float  atr,
    float  prior_vah,
    float  prior_val,
    float  prior_poc_level,
    int    prior_close_inside,
    bool   prior_poc_tested) =>

    float score = 0.0
    int   bias  = 0

    if na(poc) or na(vah) or na(val) or na(price)
        [0.0, 0]
    else
        float va_width  = vah - val
        float mid_va    = val + va_width * 0.5
        float prox_atr  = atr * 0.5   // within 0.5 ATR = "at level"

        // ── CURRENT SESSION LEVEL SCORING (75 pts max) ──────────────────────
        // Position relative to VA — 25 pts
        if price > vah + prox_atr
            score += 25.0   // Breakout above VA
            bias  := 1
        else if price < val - prox_atr
            score += 25.0   // Breakdown below VA
            bias  := -1
        else if math.abs(price - vah) < prox_atr
            score += 18.0   // Probing VAH
            bias  := price > poc ? 1 : -1
        else if math.abs(price - val) < prox_atr
            score += 18.0   // Probing VAL
            bias  := price > poc ? 1 : -1
        else if math.abs(price - poc) < prox_atr
            score += 12.0   // At POC
            bias  := 0
        else
            score += 8.0    // Inside VA

        // Profile shape — 20 pts
        score += profile_shape == "P" or profile_shape == "b" ? 20.0 :
                 profile_shape == "D"                         ? 12.0 : 5.0

        if profile_shape == "P" and bias == 0
            bias := -1
        if profile_shape == "b" and bias == 0
            bias := 1

        // VA breathing state — 20 pts
        score += va_state == "Contracting" ? 20.0 :
                 va_state == "Expanding"   ? 15.0 :
                 va_state == "Stable"      ? 10.0 : 4.0

        // Skewness — 10 pts
        float skew_deviation = math.abs(skewness - 1.0)
        score += skew_deviation > 0.4 ? 10.0 :
                 skew_deviation > 0.2 ?  7.0 :
                 skew_deviation > 0.1 ?  4.0 : 0.0

        // ── PRIOR SESSION CONTEXT SCORING (25 pts max) ──────────────────────
        if not na(prior_vah) and not na(prior_val)
            // 80% Rule: Accepted inside prior VA (boost score)
            if prior_close_inside >= 3 and price <= prior_vah and price >= prior_val
                score += 8.0
            
            // Interaction at edges
            if math.abs(price - prior_vah) < atr * 0.3
                score += 5.0
                bias  := price < prior_vah ? -1 : bias // Bearish rejection if under
            if math.abs(price - prior_val) < atr * 0.3
                score += 5.0
                bias  := price > prior_val ? 1 : bias  // Bullish support if above

            // Naked POC Magnet
            if not na(prior_poc_level) and not prior_poc_tested
                if math.abs(price - prior_poc_level) < atr * 1.0
                    score += 7.0
                    if bias == 0
                        bias := price > prior_poc_level ? -1 : 1

            // Breakout Confluence
            if price > vah and price > prior_vah
                score += 5.0
                bias  := 1

        [f_clamp(score), bias]


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// L3 — ORDER FLOW INTELLIGENCE SCORER
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// @param flow_pressure    float  Buy/sell pressure -100 to +100
// @param delta_strength   float  CVD rate-of-change momentum -100 to +100
// @param normalized_cvd   float  Session-normalized CVD 0–100
// @param absorption       bool   Absorption detected
// @param exhaustion       bool   Exhaustion detected
// @param iceberg          bool   Iceberg order detected
// @param bear_div         bool   Bearish CVD divergence
// @param bull_div         bool   Bullish CVD divergence
// @param smd_dist         bool   Smart money distribution active
// @param smd_accum        bool   Smart money accumulation active
// @param stacked_imb      int    Count of stacked imbalance zones this bar
// @returns [score 0–100, directional_bias 1/-1/0]
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
export f_score_orderflow(
    float flow_pressure,
    float delta_strength,
    float normalized_cvd,
    bool  absorption,
    bool  exhaustion,
    bool  iceberg,
    bool  bear_div,
    bool  bull_div,
    bool  smd_dist,
    bool  smd_accum,
    int   stacked_imb) =>

    float score = 0.0
    int   bias  = 0

    // Flow pressure magnitude — 25 pts
    // High pressure (abs > 50) = directional conviction
    float fp_abs = math.abs(flow_pressure)
    score += fp_abs > 75 ? 25.0 :
             fp_abs > 50 ? 20.0 :
             fp_abs > 30 ? 12.0 :
             fp_abs > 15 ?  6.0 : 0.0
    if flow_pressure > 15
        bias := 1
    else if flow_pressure < -15
        bias := -1

    // Delta strength (CVD acceleration) — 20 pts
    // Accelerating order flow = increasing conviction
    float ds_abs = math.abs(delta_strength)
    score += ds_abs > 60 ? 20.0 :
             ds_abs > 40 ? 15.0 :
             ds_abs > 20 ? 8.0  : 2.0

    // If delta_strength contradicts flow_pressure direction — conflict penalty
    bool ds_fp_conflict = (delta_strength > 20 and flow_pressure < -20) or
                          (delta_strength < -20 and flow_pressure > 20)
    if ds_fp_conflict
        score -= 10.0

    // CVD position (normalized 0–100) — 15 pts
    // Extremes (near 0 or 100) = accumulation/distribution complete = exhaustion risk
    // Mid-range with momentum = healthy directional flow
    float cvd_mid_distance = math.abs(normalized_cvd - 50.0)
    score += cvd_mid_distance > 35 ? 10.0 :    // at extreme — context is clear
             cvd_mid_distance > 20 ?  8.0 :
             cvd_mid_distance > 10 ?  4.0 : 2.0

    // Institutional signatures — 25 pts total
    // Absorption: smart money defending a level — very high context
    score += absorption ? 10.0 : 0.0
    // Iceberg: hidden wall — strong hidden conviction
    score += iceberg    ?  8.0 : 0.0
    // Stacked imbalances: institutional footprint
    score += stacked_imb >= 3 ? 10.0 :
             stacked_imb >= 1 ?  5.0 : 0.0

    // SMD flags — 12 pts, mutually exclusive guard (v1.1 FIX 5)
    // Distribution and accumulation are definitionally opposite. If both fire
    // simultaneously it is a data conflict — add small neutral context score
    // only, no directional bias commit on either side.
    if smd_dist and not smd_accum
        score += 12.0
        bias   := bias == 0 ? -1 : bias   // SMD dist = bearish pre-signal
    else if smd_accum and not smd_dist
        score += 12.0
        bias   := bias == 0 ? 1  : bias   // SMD accum = bullish pre-signal
    else if smd_dist and smd_accum
        score += 4.0                       // Contradictory signals — modest context, no bias

    // Divergence — subtract from directional confidence but ADD context value
    // (divergence = high context, just conflict context)
    score += (bear_div or bull_div) ? 5.0 : 0.0
    if exhaustion
        score -= 8.0   // Exhaustion = context is deteriorating / move ending

    // FIX v1.2 [2]: Semantic floor for "something happened, just contradictory."
    // Combined ds_fp_conflict (-10) + exhaustion (-8) can push score to -18
    // before f_clamp(). That makes deeply conflicted + exhausted flow invisible
    // (score 0) — identical to the "no order flow data" case. These are
    // semantically different. A minimum of 5.0 ensures the CIE can distinguish
    // "conflicted signal present" from "no signal at all" in the L3 sub-score.
    // Only applied when at least one meaningful input was non-default.
    bool _any_of_input = fp_abs > 15 or ds_abs > 20 or absorption or iceberg or
                         smd_dist or smd_accum or bear_div or bull_div or stacked_imb > 0
    if _any_of_input
        score := math.max(5.0, score)

    [f_clamp(score), bias]


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// L4 — LIQUIDITY INTELLIGENCE SCORER
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// @param bull_sweep      bool   ZZ structural bull sweep active
// @param bear_sweep      bool   ZZ structural bear sweep active
// @param hi_conv_bull    bool   SWEEP+FA high-conviction bull
// @param hi_conv_bear    bool   SWEEP+FA high-conviction bear
// @param fa_bull         bool   Failed auction bull (sell failure)
// @param fa_bear         bool   Failed auction bear (buy failure)
// @param ifvg_flip_bull  bool   IFVG polarity flip to bullish (new support)
// @param ifvg_flip_bear  bool   IFVG polarity flip to bearish (new resistance)
// @returns [score 0–100, directional_bias 1/-1/0]
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
export f_score_liquidity(
    bool bull_sweep,
    bool bear_sweep,
    bool hi_conv_bull,
    bool hi_conv_bear,
    bool fa_bull,
    bool fa_bear,
    bool ifvg_flip_bull,
    bool ifvg_flip_bear) =>

    float score = 0.0
    int   bias  = 0

    // SWEEP+FA = maximum liquidity context (sweep hunt complete + failed auction)
    if hi_conv_bull
        score += 60.0
        bias  := 1
    else if hi_conv_bear
        score += 60.0
        bias  := -1

    // Standalone ZZ sweep — high context but needs confirmation
    else if bull_sweep
        score += 40.0
        bias  := 1
    else if bear_sweep
        score += 40.0
        bias  := -1

    // Failed auction alone — strong context
    if fa_bull and not hi_conv_bull
        score += 25.0
        bias   := bias == 0 ? 1 : bias
    if fa_bear and not hi_conv_bear
        score += 25.0
        bias   := bias == 0 ? -1 : bias

    // IFVG polarity flip — zone changed character (adds 20 pts, confirms direction)
    // v1.3.1 PATCH #5: Added hi_conv guards, consistent with fa_bull/fa_bear pattern.
    // When SWEEP+FA (hi_conv) already fired, L4 is at 60 pts — an IFVG flip on
    // the same bar is redundant confluence that was pushing L4 to 80 and forcing
    // composite to max-conviction regardless of L2/L3 state. If a standalone IFVG
    // flip fires WITHOUT hi_conv, the full 20 pts remain appropriate.
    if ifvg_flip_bull and not hi_conv_bull
        score += 20.0
        bias   := bias == 0 ? 1 : bias
    if ifvg_flip_bear and not hi_conv_bear
        score += 20.0
        bias   := bias == 0 ? -1 : bias

    // No liquidity event = true zero (v1.1 FIX 4)
    // Removed 15-pt floor. L4 can now score 0, which lets f_top_driver
    // correctly identify when liquidity is genuinely absent as a driver.

    [f_clamp(score), bias]


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// L5 — MOMENTUM INTELLIGENCE SCORER
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// @param ma_bull_aligned  bool   Fast/Medium/Slow MAs in full bull stack order
// @param ma_bear_aligned  bool   Fast/Medium/Slow MAs in full bear stack order
// @param rotation_factor  float  POC rotation score (positive = up, negative = down)
// @param delta_strength   float  CVD rate-of-change -100 to +100
// @param ma_partial_align int    Fast vs Medium MA relationship (tri-state):
//                                  1 = fast > med  → partial bull stack
//                                 -1 = fast < med  → partial bear stack
//                                  0 = flat/entangled/na → no partial conviction
//                                Derive at call site:
//                                  not na(ma_fast) and not na(ma_medium)
//                                      ? (ma_fast > ma_medium ? 1
//                                       : ma_fast < ma_medium ? -1 : 0)
//                                      : 0
// @returns [score 0–100, directional_bias 1/-1/0]
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
export f_score_momentum(
    bool  ma_bull_aligned,
    bool  ma_bear_aligned,
    float rotation_factor,
    float delta_strength,
    int   ma_partial_align) =>

    float score = 0.0
    int   bias  = 0

    // Full MA stack alignment — 45 pts (strongest momentum signal)
    if ma_bull_aligned
        score += 45.0
        bias  := 1
    else if ma_bear_aligned
        score += 45.0
        bias  := -1
    // Partial alignment — 18 pts, three genuinely distinct states (v1.3 FIX 1)
    // ma_partial_align is a tri-state int so all three branches below are reachable.
    // Previously a bool parameter made the "flat/entangled" case unreachable.
    else if ma_partial_align == 1
        score += 18.0
        bias  :=  1
    else if ma_partial_align == -1
        score += 18.0
        bias  := -1
    // else: ma_partial_align == 0 — flat, entangled, or na
    //       score += 0, bias stays 0 — genuinely reachable now

    // Rotation factor — 30 pts (POC migrating = genuine trend)
    float rot_abs = math.abs(rotation_factor)
    score += rot_abs > 0.6 ? 30.0 :
             rot_abs > 0.4 ? 22.0 :
             rot_abs > 0.2 ? 14.0 :
             rot_abs > 0.1 ?  6.0 : 0.0

    if rotation_factor > 0.1 and bias == 0
        bias :=  1
    else if rotation_factor < -0.1 and bias == 0
        bias := -1

    // Delta strength momentum — 12.5 pts (v1.3.1 PATCH #4: halved from 25)
    // delta_strength already contributes up to 20 pts in L3 (f_score_orderflow).
    // Double-counting the same input across L3 (weight 25%) + L5 (weight 15%)
    // inflated composite by up to 8.75 pts from a single signal, causing
    // premature high_conviction flags on strong CVD runs without VP/structure
    // confirmation. L5 is an MA+momentum layer — delta strength acts here as
    // a confirmer only, so half-weight is semantically correct.
    float ds_abs = math.abs(delta_strength)
    score += ds_abs > 60 ? 12.5 :
             ds_abs > 40 ?  9.0 :
             ds_abs > 20 ?  5.0 : 1.5

    [f_clamp(score), bias]


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// L6 — SESSION INTELLIGENCE SCORER
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// @param session_bar_count  int    Bars elapsed in current session
// @param is_intraday        bool   Is the chart on an intraday timeframe
// @param tf_multiplier      int    Timeframe multiplier in minutes
// @param expected_session_bars int  Caller-derived expected bars for the active session
// @returns score 0–100 (no directional bias — session is a timing filter only)
//
// v1.1 NOTE: va_state removed from L6 (was double-counted from L2 which
// already scores it for up to 25 pts). L6 is now a pure session-timing
// filter. No va_state parameter needed.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
export f_score_session(
    int    session_bar_count,
    bool   is_intraday,
    int    tf_multiplier,
    int    expected_session_bars) =>

    // Pure session timing curve — no VP state (that belongs to L2).
    // Normalize bar count against expected bars for the timeframe.
    // Caller-derived session length keeps L6 aligned with Tokyo/London/New York,
    // Daily/Weekly/Monthly/etc., and actual completed session lengths.
    int _session_mins  = (syminfo.type == "crypto" or syminfo.type == "forex") ? 1440 : 390
    int fallback_bars  = is_intraday ? math.max(10, math.round(_session_mins / math.max(1, tf_multiplier))) : 50
    int expected_bars  = expected_session_bars > 0 ? expected_session_bars : fallback_bars
    float age_pct      = session_bar_count > 0 ? math.min(1.0, session_bar_count / expected_bars) : 0.0

    // Session age score curve:
    // 0–10%:  Opening noise — low context, gaps/spikes common         →  20 pts
    // 10–25%: Context building — profile forming, directional emerging → 40 pts
    // 25–65%: Peak RTH activity — highest signal quality window        → 80 pts
    // 65–85%: Late session — still valid, momentum slowing             → 55 pts
    // 85–100%: Closing fade — position squaring noise, avoid           → 25 pts
    float score = age_pct < 0.10 ? 20.0 :
                  age_pct < 0.25 ? 40.0 :
                  age_pct < 0.65 ? 80.0 :
                  age_pct < 0.85 ? 55.0 : 25.0

    f_clamp(score)


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// INTERNAL: Phase classifier from sub-scores + bias votes
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// REFACTOR v1.3: bull_votes and bear_votes are now passed in from analyze_context
// rather than recomputed here. analyze_context already counts them for the
// RANGING_NOISE composite check — computing them again here was redundant.
// The five individual bias params (struct_bias … liq_bias) are removed;
// callers pass the already-tallied vote integers.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
f_classify_phase(
    float  composite,
    int    bull_votes,    // pre-computed in analyze_context
    int    bear_votes,    // pre-computed in analyze_context
    float  l1,
    float  l2,
    float  l3,
    float  l4,
    float  l5,
    bool   hi_conv_bull,
    bool   hi_conv_bear,
    bool   bull_choch,
    bool   bear_choch,
    bool   bull_sweep,
    bool   bear_sweep,
    bool   smd_dist,
    bool   smd_accum,
    string va_state,
    float  rotation_factor) =>

    int bias = bull_votes > bear_votes ? 1 : bear_votes > bull_votes ? -1 : 0

    // v1.3.1 PATCH #3: Pre-compute SMD l3 gate BEFORE the if/else chain.
    // Cannot declare variables mid-chain in Pine v6 — declaration breaks the
    // else-if linkage (CE10156). Dual-threshold: l3 > 50 on normal bars,
    // l3 > 20 during EMA warmup (composite < 40) so SMD events are not swallowed
    // by RANGING_NOISE on the exact session-open bars they matter most.
    bool _smd_l3_gate = composite >= 40 ? l3 > 50 : l3 > 20

    // Phase classification — priority order matters
    string phase = ""

    if hi_conv_bull or hi_conv_bear
        // Highest: SWEEP + FA coinciding — maximum institutional confluence
        phase := hi_conv_bull ? "SWEEP+FA BULL" : "SWEEP+FA BEAR"

    else if bull_choch or bear_choch
        // Structure trend flip confirmed.
        // FIX v1.2 [3]: CHoCH booleans must only be true on the confirmation bar.
        // EliteMA_ATRZigZag guarantees single-bar events, but as a defensive guard
        // we only promote to STRUCTURE_FLIP if the CHoCH fires alongside meaningful
        // structure score (l1 > 20). A stale CHoCH with degraded structure score
        // indicates persistence from a prior bar and should fall through to lower
        // priority phases rather than override a high-composite trending environment.
        phase := (l1 > 20) ? (bull_choch ? "STRUCTURE_FLIP_BULL" : "STRUCTURE_FLIP_BEAR")
                           : (composite >= 75 and bull_votes >= 4 ? "TRENDING_ALIGNED_BULL"
                              : composite >= 75 and bear_votes >= 4 ? "TRENDING_ALIGNED_BEAR"
                              : "NEUTRAL")

    // FIX v1.2 [4]: DISTRIBUTION / ACCUMULATION now checked BEFORE TRENDING_ALIGNED.
    // SMD events are higher-order institutional signals than a generic trending phase.
    // Old order caused TRENDING_ALIGNED_BULL to suppress active DISTRIBUTION at 75+ score,
    // hiding the precise warning the trader needs. Gate uses _smd_l3_gate (see above).
    else if smd_dist and _smd_l3_gate
        // Smart money distributing into imbalance — pre-move bearish context
        phase := "DISTRIBUTION"

    else if smd_accum and _smd_l3_gate
        // Smart money accumulating into imbalance — pre-move bullish context
        phase := "ACCUMULATION"

    else if composite >= 75 and bull_votes >= 4
        phase := "TRENDING_ALIGNED_BULL"

    else if composite >= 75 and bear_votes >= 4
        phase := "TRENDING_ALIGNED_BEAR"

    else if (bull_sweep or bear_sweep) and l4 > 35
        // Liquidity hunt in progress — wait for confirmation
        phase := bull_sweep ? "LIQUIDITY_HUNT_BULL" : "LIQUIDITY_HUNT_BEAR"

    else if va_state == "Contracting" and l2 > 40 and composite > 50
        // VA coiling — expansion setup loading
        phase := "EXPANSION_IMMINENT"

    else if math.abs(rotation_factor) > 0.3 and l5 > 50
        // Momentum with rotation — trending but not fully aligned
        phase := bias == 1 ? "TRENDING_BULL" : "TRENDING_BEAR"

    else if composite < 40 or math.abs(bull_votes - bear_votes) == 0
        // Low score OR perfectly tied votes — genuine noise / no directional conviction.
        // v1.1 FIX 3: was <= 1 which incorrectly flagged 3-2 vote leans as RANGING_NOISE.
        // A one-vote margin (e.g. 3-2) is a real directional lean and should not close gates.
        phase := "RANGING_NOISE"

    else
        phase := bias == 1 ? "MILD_BULL" : bias == -1 ? "MILD_BEAR" : "NEUTRAL"

    [phase, bias]


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// INTERNAL: Top driver identifier (which layer is contributing most)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
f_top_driver(float l1, float l2, float l3, float l4, float l5, float l6) =>
    float w1 = l1 * 0.25
    float w2 = l2 * 0.20
    float w3 = l3 * 0.25
    float w4 = l4 * 0.10
    float w5 = l5 * 0.15
    float w6 = l6 * 0.05

    float mx = math.max(w1, math.max(w2, math.max(w3, math.max(w4, math.max(w5, w6)))))

    // v1.3.1 PATCH #10: Tie-break order is intentional — left-to-right evaluation
    // means STRUCTURE > VOL_PROFILE > ORDER_FLOW > LIQUIDITY > MOMENTUM > SESSION
    // on exact ties. Structure is the highest-priority layer by design (price action
    // framework foundation), so its tie-break preference is architecturally correct.
    // This is documented here to prevent future "fix" attempts on non-bugs.
    mx == w1 ? "STRUCTURE" : mx == w2 ? "VOL_PROFILE" : mx == w3 ? "ORDER_FLOW" : mx == w4 ? "LIQUIDITY" : mx == w5 ? "MOMENTUM" : "SESSION"


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// INTERNAL: Phase → Color mapping
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
f_phase_color(string phase) =>
    switch phase
        "SWEEP+FA BULL"          => color.new(color.lime, 0)
        "SWEEP+FA BEAR"          => color.new(color.red,  0)
        "STRUCTURE_FLIP_BULL"    => color.new(color.green, 10)
        "STRUCTURE_FLIP_BEAR"    => color.new(color.fuchsia, 10)
        "TRENDING_ALIGNED_BULL"  => color.new(color.lime, 20)
        "TRENDING_ALIGNED_BEAR"  => color.new(color.red,  20)
        "TRENDING_BULL"          => color.new(color.teal, 20)
        "TRENDING_BEAR"          => color.new(color.orange, 20)
        "DISTRIBUTION"           => color.new(color.orange, 10)
        "ACCUMULATION"           => color.new(color.teal, 10)
        "LIQUIDITY_HUNT_BULL"    => color.new(color.yellow, 20)
        "LIQUIDITY_HUNT_BEAR"    => color.new(color.yellow, 20)
        "EXPANSION_IMMINENT"     => color.new(color.purple, 10)
        "MILD_BULL"              => color.new(color.green, 50)
        "MILD_BEAR"              => color.new(color.red,   50)
        "NEUTRAL"                => color.new(color.gray,  30)
        =>                          color.new(color.gray,  60)   // RANGING_NOISE


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// INTERNAL: Signal gate logic
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// OPEN    → score >= 70 and layers not conflicted
// CAUTION → score 45–69 or single-layer conflict
// CLOSED  → score < 45 or RANGING_NOISE phase
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
f_signal_gate(float score, string phase, bool conflict) =>
    phase == "RANGING_NOISE" ? "CLOSED" : score >= 70 and not conflict  ? "OPEN"    : score >= 45               ? "CAUTION" : "CLOSED"


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// MASTER EXPORT: analyze_context
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Single call that runs all 6 layers and returns the full ContextState.
// All inputs must be passed explicitly from the main indicator.
//
// ── L1 STRUCTURE ──
// @param zz_score_long    float  Structure quality score for longs (0–100)
// @param zz_score_short   float  Structure quality score for shorts (0–100)
// @param struct_bias      int    ZZ structural bias 1/-1/0
// @param bull_bos         bool   BOS bull fired this bar
// @param bear_bos         bool   BOS bear fired this bar
// @param bull_choch       bool   CHoCH bull fired this bar
// @param bear_choch       bool   CHoCH bear fired this bar
// @param hi_conv_bull     bool   SWEEP+FA bull high-conviction
// @param hi_conv_bear     bool   SWEEP+FA bear high-conviction
//
// ── L2 VOL PROFILE ──
// @param poc              float  Point of Control price
// @param vah              float  Value Area High
// @param val              float  Value Area Low
// @param profile_shape    string "P" / "b" / "D" / "Balanced"
// @param va_state         string "Expanding" / "Contracting" / "Stable" / "Neutral"
// @param skewness         float  Profile skewness ratio
//
// ── L3 ORDER FLOW ──
// @param flow_pressure    float  Buy-sell pressure -100 to +100
// @param delta_strength   float  CVD rate-of-change -100 to +100
// @param normalized_cvd   float  Session CVD normalized 0–100
// @param absorption       bool   Absorption signal
// @param exhaustion       bool   Exhaustion signal
// @param iceberg          bool   Iceberg detection
// @param bear_div         bool   Bearish CVD divergence
// @param bull_div         bool   Bullish CVD divergence
// @param smd_dist         bool   Smart money distribution
// @param smd_accum        bool   Smart money accumulation
// @param stacked_imb      int    Stacked imbalance zone count
//
// ── L4 LIQUIDITY ──
// @param bull_sweep       bool   ZZ bull structural sweep
// @param bear_sweep       bool   ZZ bear structural sweep
// @param fa_bull          bool   Failed auction bull
// @param fa_bear          bool   Failed auction bear
// @param ifvg_flip_bull   bool   IFVG flipped to bullish support this bar
// @param ifvg_flip_bear   bool   IFVG flipped to bearish resistance this bar
//
// ── L5 MOMENTUM ──
// @param ma_bull_aligned  bool   Full bull MA stack
// @param ma_bear_aligned  bool   Full bear MA stack
// @param rotation_factor  float  POC rotation (positive = up)
// @param ma_partial_align int    Fast vs Medium MA tri-state: 1=bull / -1=bear / 0=flat
//
// ── L6 SESSION ──
// @param session_bar_count int   Bars elapsed in current session
// @param is_intraday       bool  Is the chart intraday
// @param tf_multiplier     int   Timeframe multiplier (minutes)
// @param expected_session_bars int Caller-derived expected bars for this session type
//                                NOTE: va_state removed from L6 in v1.1 (was double-counted
//                                from L2). L6 is now a pure timing filter.
//
// ── GLOBAL ──
// @param current_atr       float Current ATR(14) value
// @param price             float Current price (close)
// @param conviction_threshold simple float Score threshold for high_conviction (default 70)
//
// @returns ContextState
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
export analyze_context(
    // L1
    float zz_score_long,
    float zz_score_short,
    int   struct_bias,
    bool  bull_bos,
    bool  bear_bos,
    bool  bull_choch,
    bool  bear_choch,
    bool  hi_conv_bull,
    bool  hi_conv_bear,
    // L2
    float  poc,
    float  vah,
    float  val,
    string profile_shape,
    string va_state,
    float  skewness,
    // Phase 3: Prior VA Context
    float  prior_vah,
    float  prior_val,
    float  prior_poc_level,
    int    prior_close_inside,
    bool   prior_poc_tested,
    // L3
    float flow_pressure,
    float delta_strength,
    float normalized_cvd,
    bool  absorption,
    bool  exhaustion,
    bool  iceberg,
    bool  bear_div,
    bool  bull_div,
    bool  smd_dist,
    bool  smd_accum,
    int   stacked_imb,
    // L4
    bool bull_sweep,
    bool bear_sweep,
    bool fa_bull,
    bool fa_bear,
    bool ifvg_flip_bull,
    bool ifvg_flip_bear,
    // L5
    bool  ma_bull_aligned,
    bool  ma_bear_aligned,
    float rotation_factor,
    int   ma_partial_align,
    // L6
    int  session_bar_count,
    bool is_intraday,
    int  tf_multiplier,
    int  expected_session_bars,
    // Global
    float current_atr,
    float price,
    simple float conviction_threshold = 70.0) =>

    // ── Run all 6 scorers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    [l1, bias1] = f_score_structure(
        zz_score_long, zz_score_short, struct_bias,
        bull_bos, bear_bos, bull_choch, bear_choch,
        hi_conv_bull, hi_conv_bear)

    [l2, bias2] = f_score_vp(
        poc, vah, val, profile_shape, va_state, skewness, price, current_atr,
        prior_vah, prior_val, prior_poc_level, prior_close_inside, prior_poc_tested)

    [l3, bias3] = f_score_orderflow(
        flow_pressure, delta_strength, normalized_cvd,
        absorption, exhaustion, iceberg,
        bear_div, bull_div, smd_dist, smd_accum, stacked_imb)

    [l4, bias4] = f_score_liquidity(
        bull_sweep, bear_sweep, hi_conv_bull, hi_conv_bear,
        fa_bull, fa_bear, ifvg_flip_bull, ifvg_flip_bear)

    [l5, bias5] = f_score_momentum(
        ma_bull_aligned, ma_bear_aligned, rotation_factor,
        delta_strength, ma_partial_align)

    float l6 = f_score_session(session_bar_count, is_intraday, tf_multiplier, expected_session_bars)

    // ── Weighted composite ────────────────────────────────────────────────
    float composite = f_clamp(
        l1 * 0.25 +
        l2 * 0.20 +
        l3 * 0.25 +
        l4 * 0.10 +
        l5 * 0.15 +
        l6 * 0.05)

    // ── Composite smoothing (v1.1 FIX 6) ─────────────────────────────────
    // Light EMA prevents bar-to-bar gate flipping from boolean-heavy inputs.
    // Gates and high_conviction use smoothed value; raw composite goes to HUD.
    //
    // SINGLETON GUARD (AUDIT): _smooth_comp is a module-level var —
    // a single shared EMA instance for the entire script. analyze_context()
    // MUST be called from exactly one location per importing script. Calling
    // it from two sites (e.g. in a comparison test) will corrupt both callers'
    // EMA state. The guard below detects double-calls on the same bar.
    var float _smooth_comp       = na
    var int   _singleton_last_bi = -1
    if _singleton_last_bi == bar_index
        // Second call on same bar — EMA already advanced once this bar.
        // Warn via log.warning if available; silently degrade otherwise.
        // The composite will be double-smoothed but won't crash.
        log.warning("⚠️ CIE analyze_context() called twice on bar " + str.tostring(bar_index) + " — EMA corrupted. Ensure single call site.")
    _singleton_last_bi := bar_index
    _smooth_comp    := na(_smooth_comp) ? composite : _smooth_comp * 0.7 + composite * 0.3
    float gating_composite = _smooth_comp

    // ── Conflict detection (v1.1 FIX 2) ──────────────────────────────────
    // Layer-weight-aware scoring. L6 excluded (directionally neutral).
    // Conflict fires when both directions have meaningful weight AND
    // weighted difference is ≤ 0.15 (roughly equal split).
    float bull_weight = (bias1 ==  1 ? 0.25 : 0.0) + (bias2 ==  1 ? 0.20 : 0.0) + (bias3 ==  1 ? 0.25 : 0.0) + (bias4 ==  1 ? 0.10 : 0.0) + (bias5 ==  1 ? 0.15 : 0.0)
    float bear_weight = (bias1 == -1 ? 0.25 : 0.0) + (bias2 == -1 ? 0.20 : 0.0) + (bias3 == -1 ? 0.25 : 0.0) + (bias4 == -1 ? 0.10 : 0.0) + (bias5 == -1 ? 0.15 : 0.0)
    bool conflict = bull_weight > 0.0 and bear_weight > 0.0 and math.abs(bull_weight - bear_weight) <= 0.15

    // ── Pre-compute integer vote counts (REFACTOR v1.3) ───────────────────
    // These are the simple unweighted counts used by f_classify_phase for
    // threshold checks (e.g. bull_votes >= 4). Computed once here and passed
    // in — f_classify_phase no longer recounts from individual bias params.
    int bull_votes = (bias1 ==  1 ? 1 : 0) + (bias2 ==  1 ? 1 : 0) +
                     (bias3 ==  1 ? 1 : 0) + (bias4 ==  1 ? 1 : 0) + (bias5 ==  1 ? 1 : 0)
    int bear_votes = (bias1 == -1 ? 1 : 0) + (bias2 == -1 ? 1 : 0) +
                     (bias3 == -1 ? 1 : 0) + (bias4 == -1 ? 1 : 0) + (bias5 == -1 ? 1 : 0)

    // ── Phase + bias ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    [phase, bias] = f_classify_phase(
        composite, bull_votes, bear_votes,
        l1, l2, l3, l4, l5,
        hi_conv_bull, hi_conv_bear, bull_choch, bear_choch,
        bull_sweep, bear_sweep, smd_dist, smd_accum,
        va_state, rotation_factor)

    // ── Derive output fields ──────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Gates use gating_composite (smoothed). score field = raw for HUD display.
    string gate       = f_signal_gate(gating_composite, phase, conflict)
    color  p_color    = f_phase_color(phase)
    string top_driver = f_top_driver(l1, l2, l3, l4, l5, l6)
    bool   hi_conv    = gating_composite >= conviction_threshold

    // Named field initialization (REFACTOR v1.3) — order-change-safe.
    ContextState.new(
        phase            = phase,
        score            = composite,
        bias             = bias,
        high_conviction  = hi_conv,
        signal_gate      = gate,
        phase_color      = p_color,
        l1_structure     = l1,
        l2_vp            = l2,
        l3_orderflow     = l3,
        l4_liquidity     = l4,
        l5_momentum      = l5,
        l6_session       = l6,
        top_driver       = top_driver,
        conflict_detected = conflict)


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// EXPORT: Signal-specific gate queries
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// These are the per-signal convenience wrappers the main indicator calls
// to decide whether a given signal type should render / alert.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// @function Returns true if FVG touch signals should be considered valid.
// FVGs require structure alignment + non-noise order flow + not in RANGING_NOISE.
// @param this  ContextState  Output from analyze_context()
// @param dir   int           Signal direction: 1 = bull, -1 = bear, 0 = neutral (default)
// @returns bool
export method gate_fvg(ContextState this, int dir = 0) =>
    bool magnitude_ok = this.signal_gate != "CLOSED" and this.l1_structure >= 40.0 and this.l3_orderflow >= 35.0 and this.phase != "RANGING_NOISE"
    bool direction_ok = dir == 0 or (dir == 1 ? this.bias >= 0 : this.bias <= 0)
    magnitude_ok and direction_ok


// @function Returns true if VP level (POC/VAH/VAL) signals should fire.
// VP levels require order flow confirmation + non-conflicted context.
// @param this  ContextState  Output from analyze_context()
// @param dir   int           Signal direction: 1 = bull, -1 = bear, 0 = neutral (default)
// @returns bool
export method gate_vp_level(ContextState this, int dir = 0) =>
    bool magnitude_ok = this.signal_gate != "CLOSED" and this.l2_vp >= 45.0 and this.l3_orderflow >= 30.0 and not this.conflict_detected
    bool direction_ok = dir == 0 or (dir == 1 ? this.bias >= 0 : this.bias <= 0)
    magnitude_ok and direction_ok


// @function Returns true if BOS/CHoCH entry signals should be acted on.
// Structure breaks require momentum + flow pressure confirmation.
// STRUCTURE_FLIP phases bypass conflict gate: CHoCH fires as conflict resolves —
// transitional bar still has conflict=true, which would otherwise block the
// gate on exactly the bar you most need it open.
// @param this      ContextState  Output from analyze_context()
// @param is_choch  bool          Pass true for CHoCH call sites (relaxed CAUTION-ok rule).
// @param dir       int           Signal direction: 1 = bull, -1 = bear, 0 = neutral (default)
// @returns bool
export method gate_structure_break(ContextState this, bool is_choch = false, int dir = 0) =>
    bool is_correct_flip = (dir == 1 and this.phase == "STRUCTURE_FLIP_BULL") or
                           (dir == -1 and this.phase == "STRUCTURE_FLIP_BEAR")
    bool score_ok = this.l1_structure >= 55.0 and this.l5_momentum  >= 40.0 and this.l3_orderflow >= 35.0
    bool phase_ok = this.phase != "RANGING_NOISE"
    // CHoCH: CAUTION gate is sufficient — it fires as consolidation breaks.
    // BOS:   OPEN gate required — it confirms an already-trending environment.
    bool gate_ok  = is_choch ? this.signal_gate != "CLOSED" : this.signal_gate == "OPEN"
    bool direction_ok = dir == 0 or (dir == 1 ? this.bias >= 0 : this.bias <= 0)
    is_correct_flip or (gate_ok and score_ok and phase_ok and direction_ok)


// @function Returns true if MA cross / trend-following signals should fire.
// MA crosses require full trend alignment and no conflict.
// @param this  ContextState  Output from analyze_context()
// @param dir   int           Signal direction: 1 = bull, -1 = bear, 0 = neutral (default)
// @returns bool
export method gate_ma_cross(ContextState this, int dir = 0) =>
    bool magnitude_ok = this.signal_gate == "OPEN" and this.l5_momentum  >= 50.0 and this.l1_structure >= 45.0 and not this.conflict_detected
    bool direction_ok = dir == 0 or (dir == 1 ? this.bias >= 0 : this.bias <= 0)
    magnitude_ok and direction_ok


// @function Returns true if liquidity sweep reversal setups should fire.
// Sweeps require high liquidity score + order flow shift confirmation.
// @param this  ContextState  Output from analyze_context()
// @param dir   int           Signal direction: 1 = bull, -1 = bear, 0 = neutral (default)
// @returns bool
export method gate_sweep_reversal(ContextState this, int dir = 0) =>
    bool magnitude_ok = this.l4_liquidity >= 40.0 and this.l3_orderflow >= 30.0 and this.signal_gate  != "CLOSED"
    bool direction_ok = dir == 0 or (dir == 1 ? this.bias >= 0 : this.bias <= 0)
    magnitude_ok and direction_ok


